      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercially validated FEA solver with documented verification test suite; version-controlled analysis environment.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2021 R2 used under an FDA-qualified software framework. Solver verification suite results on file; analysis environment controlled via configuration management system meeting 21 CFR Part 11 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems spanning linear elastic contact and large-displacement beam bending solved to within 1% of analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "Three benchmark cases (Hertzian contact, cantilever beam, threaded joint pull-out) verified against analytical and published reference solutions. Maximum error 0.7%. Code verification documented in VVP-NCV-001."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QOI change less than 2% between successive refinement levels using GCI method.",
      "rationale": "Four-level mesh refinement study performed on representative pedicle screw construct. GCI-estimated discretization error for construct stiffness QOI is 1.3%; for yield load QOI is 1.8%. Final mesh selected at refinement level 3 (1.2M elements)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error below 0.5%.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson nonlinear solver converged to force residual norm below 1e-7 for all 220 load increments across 11 model instances. Energy balance error maximum 0.18%. No divergence events recorded."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup; documented analysis procedure with mandatory checklist completion.",
      "rationale": "Two independent analysts reviewed boundary condition application, material assignment, contact pair definition, and load application for each of 11 model instances. Discrepancies resolved before results extraction. Signed checklists archived in DMS-2024-NP-007."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics assumptions (linear elastic titanium, frictional contact at screw-rod interface, rigid test fixtures) justified by literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic assumption for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) validated against published stress-strain data for loads below 0.7 times yield. Frictional contact coefficient sensitivity study shows QOI variation below 3% across mu=0.15 to 0.35. Rigid fixture assumption confirmed by fixture compliance measurement (0.4% of total displacement)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from ASTM-certified coupon testing of same material lot; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of tested specimens.",
      "rationale": "Young's modulus and Poisson's ratio from tension coupon tests (n=5, same Ti-6Al-4V lot as implants). Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements with 5-micron accuracy. Polyaxial head torque from calibrated torque wrench records. All inputs traceable to test records TR-2023-NP-001 through TR-2023-NP-011."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from same production lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design drawings within tolerance.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from a single production lot (Lot 2023-NP-A) tested across two laboratories (FDA CDRH, DePuy Synthes). All constructs dimensionally inspected; 100% within drawing tolerances. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASME V&V 40 guidance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two load levels and two construct configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending condition (5 degrees, 73.5 N axial preload) only. Clinical loading variability (patient weight, activity level, sagittal alignment) not explored experimentally. This factor is below required level; risk accepted at Medium assurance level given the conservative nature of F1717 loading relative to in vivo conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters demonstrably equivalent to experimental test parameters; any discrepancies quantified and shown to have negligible QOI impact.",
      "rationale": "Direct mapping established between CMM-measured specimen geometry and FEA geometry for all 11 constructs. Applied displacement boundary conditions matched to actuator displacement records from test data acquisition system. Torque preload on polyaxial heads matched to within 2% of measured values. Equivalency documented in EQV-2023-NP-001."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., ASME V&V 20 validation metric or percent difference) applied; FEA predictions within 10% of experimental mean for primary QOIs.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness: FEA mean 187.3 N/mm vs. experimental mean 191.2 N/mm (2.0% difference, within 10% acceptance criterion). Yield load: FEA mean 412.6 N vs. experimental mean 408.9 N (0.9% difference). ASME V&V 20 validation metric computed; model falls within experimental uncertainty band for both QOIs. Detailed comparison in OC-2023-NP-001."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOIs (construct stiffness, yield load) are the same quantities used in the regulatory submission claim and are clinically meaningful predictors of construct mechanical performance.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load under ASTM F1717 compression-bending are the primary mechanical performance endpoints in the 510(k) submission predicate comparison. These QOIs are directly linked to the regulatory decision. Relevance confirmed by FDA guidance on spinal implant mechanical testing (2021 guidance document)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activity geometry, material, loading, and boundary conditions are representative of the intended use FEA model application.",
      "rationale": "Validation constructs are identical in geometry, material, and assembly to the production device modeled in the regulatory submission FEA. Loading protocol (ASTM F1717) is the same as applied in the submission model. The only deviation is single test condition (addressed under Test conditions factor). Overall validation activity is highly representative of the COU as described in the claim and requirement documentation."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-2026-04-19",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels for Medium model risk (Level 3). One factor (Test conditions) achieves Level 2 against a required Level 3; this shortfall is accepted because ASTM F1717 compression-bending represents a conservative mechanical loading envelope relative to in vivo conditions, and the regulatory claim is bounded to this specific test configuration. The overall credibility evidence package is sufficient to support the Medium assurance level determination for a Class II device 510(k) submission. FEA predictions of construct stiffness and yield load are within 2% of experimental means across N=11 constructs at two independent laboratories.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
